# Hardware and Software Setup for Raspberry Pi NAS

This guide combines hardware preparation and software installation for a functional NAS.

## 1. Hardware Setup
1. Insert the microSD card (flashed with Raspberry Pi OS) into the Pi.
2. Place the Pi in a case with passive cooling or fan.
3. Connect Ethernet cable to router for stable network.
4. Attach external storage (HDD/SSD) via USB 3.0 enclosure.
5. Connect power supply (Official PSU recommended).

## 2. Software Installation
1. Boot the Pi with OS and complete initial configuration.
2. Update packages:
```bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt full-upgrade -y
Install essential packages:

bash
Copy code
sudo apt install -y samba samba-common exfat-fuse exfatprogs ntfs-3g htop iotop smartmontools nano git curl wget
